01:06.965 --> 01:08.630
Uhh!

01:11.465 --> 01:12.897
Uhh...

01:39.975 --> 01:41.908
This must feel like
slumming to you,

01:41.975 --> 01:44.340
speaking at my lowly
graduate seminar.

01:44.408 --> 01:47.538
Well, someone's got to set your
students straight about my work.

01:47.606 --> 01:48.839
Just pointing out
the flaws.

01:48.906 --> 01:50.406
And you're doing
a fine job.

01:50.474 --> 01:52.307
Have you two always
been like this?

01:52.374 --> 01:54.341
No, we're far more
civil now.

01:54.409 --> 01:56.909
I'd like to have seen
Lightman at Oxford.

01:56.977 --> 02:00.244
Yes. Back when he was a
real student of psychology.

02:00.312 --> 02:02.778
Are you sure you want me
sabotaging your students?

02:02.846 --> 02:04.779
No, but I don't have
another lecture ready,

02:04.847 --> 02:06.347
so you're on.

02:06.415 --> 02:07.847
Fine.

02:07.915 --> 02:09.282
Because
people have got to know

02:09.350 --> 02:10.782
whether or not their
president's a crook.

02:10.850 --> 02:12.351
Well, I'm not a crook.

02:12.418 --> 02:15.353
I've earned
everything I've got.

02:15.421 --> 02:17.188
I love this guy.

02:17.255 --> 02:21.257
You see how he's looking
down and he's nodding?

02:21.325 --> 02:23.225
He's contradicting
his own statement.

02:23.293 --> 02:26.860
He hesitates before saying
he's earned everything he's got.

02:26.927 --> 02:28.461
And notice
the crossed arms.

02:28.528 --> 02:30.262
He's defensive.

02:30.329 --> 02:32.363
Which means
he's full of it.

02:34.265 --> 02:38.200
He's not nodding his head.
He's looking down at his notes.

02:38.268 --> 02:40.369
Being defensive
doesn't mean you're lying.

02:40.437 --> 02:44.035
Well, one of these things by itself
may not be conclusive,

02:44.103 --> 02:46.298
but when you put them together,
they add up to deception.

02:46.366 --> 02:48.262
Yeah, or you're looking
for things to prove deception

02:48.330 --> 02:49.996
so you find them.

02:50.063 --> 02:52.530
And if Lincoln were showing
in the same behaviors,
would you say he was lying?

02:52.598 --> 02:55.099
I'd say he was Nixon
in a Lincoln mask.

02:56.867 --> 02:58.864
All right, let's do
a practical demonstration

02:58.932 --> 03:01.299
and then you guys
can see for yourself.

03:01.367 --> 03:02.633
We need a volunteer.

03:02.701 --> 03:04.801
How about you?
Mister, um...

03:04.868 --> 03:06.002
Martin.

03:06.069 --> 03:08.303
Martin Walker.

03:08.371 --> 03:10.037
Right.

03:12.306 --> 03:14.706
So, I've got 10 pictures.

03:14.774 --> 03:17.308
Pick one, then lie about what
you're seeing r tell the truth,

03:17.376 --> 03:19.542
and Dr. Lightman
will read you.

03:25.380 --> 03:27.313
What about stakes?

03:27.381 --> 03:29.214
I read your book,
Dr. Lightman.

03:29.282 --> 03:31.916
Without stakes,
it's hard to spot a lie.

03:31.984 --> 03:34.318
There's no fear
of being caught.

03:34.385 --> 03:35.818
All right.

03:35.886 --> 03:38.320
100 bucks says I can read you
like a book.

03:38.388 --> 03:39.821
Mm-hmm.

03:41.890 --> 03:43.557
All right.

03:45.393 --> 03:47.760
A pretty girl.

03:47.828 --> 03:50.329
College age, I'd say.

03:50.397 --> 03:53.331
Ponytail. Blonde.

03:53.399 --> 03:55.566
Big eyes.

03:56.901 --> 03:59.569
And pale, pink blouse.

04:00.905 --> 04:03.906
You like the ladies,
Martin?

04:03.974 --> 04:06.508
Yeah. What's not to like?

04:09.278 --> 04:11.078
In that case, you're talking
out your ass,

04:11.146 --> 04:15.514
'cause whatever you're seeing there
you don't like it.

04:32.053 --> 04:34.021
What do you say now,
Dr. Lightman?

04:35.857 --> 04:37.291
Double or quits.

04:37.359 --> 04:39.026
Ooh!

04:51.835 --> 04:54.236
Guy tied to a chair.

04:54.304 --> 04:56.805
He's soaking wet.

04:56.872 --> 04:59.908
Being zapped
with electric cables,

04:59.976 --> 05:02.877
like you'd use to
jump start a car.

05:06.849 --> 05:08.483
Total rubbish.

05:26.197 --> 05:29.761
Ok. I think that's it for
today's class.

05:29.829 --> 05:31.428
Our thanks to
Dr. Lightman.

05:31.494 --> 05:33.759
Always entertaining
and fascinating.

05:38.263 --> 05:40.496
We'll have to
do this again.

05:42.332 --> 05:44.768
A bad day
for Lightman way.

05:44.836 --> 05:46.770
Hey. Where
are you going?

05:46.838 --> 05:48.772
Did you put him
up to this?

05:48.839 --> 05:50.273
How could I do that?

05:50.341 --> 05:53.008
I mean, your technique
is foolproof, right?

05:58.347 --> 05:59.713
Yeah.

05:59.781 --> 06:01.715
Here's the problem.

06:01.783 --> 06:04.217
Martin Walker's
a psychopath,

06:04.285 --> 06:06.219
probably a killer.

06:06.287 --> 06:08.121
Just thought you should know.

